- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is the most likely category as the paper discusses evolutionary algorithms and their global search behavior. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is also likely as the paper proposes a new mutation operator for optimization problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is relevant as the paper discusses the performance of standard benchmark problems. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses multi-dimensional parameter control. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is less likely but still possible as the paper discusses controlling the variance of a mutation operator.
